======================================================================
OBLONG SIMPLEX VALUES = m²+m+1
======================================================================

m²+m+1 sequence (cyclotomic Φ₃(m)):
  m=0: m²+m+1 =     1,  x=m(m+1)=  0,  (x+1)=1
  m=1: m²+m+1 =     3,  x=m(m+1)=  2,  (x+1)=3
  m=2: m²+m+1 =     7,  x=m(m+1)=  6,  (x+1)=7
  m=3: m²+m+1 =    13,  x=m(m+1)= 12,  (x+1)=13
  m=4: m²+m+1 =    21,  x=m(m+1)= 20,  (x+1)=21
  m=5: m²+m+1 =    31,  x=m(m+1)= 30,  (x+1)=31
  m=6: m²+m+1 =    43,  x=m(m+1)= 42,  (x+1)=43
  m=7: m²+m+1 =    57,  x=m(m+1)= 56,  (x+1)=57
  m=8: m²+m+1 =    73,  x=m(m+1)= 72,  (x+1)=73
  m=9: m²+m+1 =    91,  x=m(m+1)= 90,  (x+1)=91

So the 'simplex at oblong' is just m²+m+1.
This is the CYCLOTOMIC POLYNOMIAL Φ₃(m) = (m³-1)/(m-1) = m²+m+1

======================================================================
WHICH Φ₃(m) VALUES ARE ACHIEVABLE AS H?
======================================================================

  Φ₃( 0) =    1  achievable
  Φ₃( 1) =    3  achievable
  Φ₃( 2) =    7  PERMANENTLY FORBIDDEN
  Φ₃( 3) =   13  achievable
  Φ₃( 4) =   21  PERMANENTLY FORBIDDEN
  Φ₃( 5) =   31  achievable
  Φ₃( 6) =   43  achievable
  Φ₃( 7) =   57  achievable
  Φ₃( 8) =   73  achievable
  Φ₃( 9) =   91  achievable
  Φ₃(10) =  111  achievable
  Φ₃(11) =  133  achievable
  Φ₃(12) =  157  achievable
  Φ₃(13) =  183  gap at n=7 (fills later)
  Φ₃(14) =  211  achievable
  Φ₃(15) =  241  achievable
  Φ₃(16) =  273  achievable
  Φ₃(17) =  307  achievable
  Φ₃(18) =  343  achievable
  Φ₃(19) =  381  achievable

REMARKABLE: The ONLY permanently forbidden Φ₃ values are m=2 and m=4!

